rega hiv 1 subtyping tool version 2.0 stanford university hiv drug resistance database a curated public database designed to represent store and analyze the divergent forms of data underlying hiv drug resistance a curated public database designed to represent store and analyze the divergent forms of data underlying hiv drug resistance home genotype rx genotype pheno genotype clinical hivdb program rega hiv 1 subtyping tool version 2.0 this tool is designed to use phylogenetic methods in order to identify the subtype of a specific sequence the sequence is analysed for recombination using bootscanning methods more information on the subtyping process note for batch analysis the rega subtype tool accepts up to 1000 sequences at a time choose a mirror to subtype your sequences enter here your input data as fasta format or click here for importing a sample sequence fasta input paste fasta format sequence in the text box below reset analyze developed by tulio de oliveira koen deforche sharon cassol andrew rambaut and anne mieke vandamme developed in cooperation with the evolutionary group at university of oxford uk the hiv 1 pathogenesis and immunotherapeutics program at university of pretoria south africa and the rega institute at the katholieke universiteit leuven leuven belgium funded by the flanders bilateral cooperation program and the wellcome trust grant 061238 please report problems and or suggestions to dr tulio de oliveira revised 3rd of october 2006 the team who we are & how to contact us publications collaborators acknowledgements the data user guide & database documents database statistics hiv related links additional resources 1998 2005 all rights reserved questions contact
